# Google Sheets API Configuration
# You'll need to create a Google Cloud Project and enable the Google Sheets API
# Then create a service account and generate a private key (JSON file)

# The ID of your Google Spreadsheet (found in the URL)
# Example: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/YOUR_SPREADSHEET_ID/edit
GOOGLE_SPREADSHEET_ID=your_spreadsheet_id_here

# Service account email from your Google Cloud Project
GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL=your-service-account@your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com

# Private key from the service account JSON file
# Note: Replace \n with actual newlines, or use the raw key with \\n
GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYOUR_PRIVATE_KEY_HERE\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"

# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console (https://console.cloud.google.com/)
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 3. Enable Google Sheets API
# 4. Create a service account (IAM & Admin > Service Accounts)
# 5. Generate a JSON key for the service account
# 6. Share your Google Spreadsheet with the service account email
# 7. Copy the values from the JSON file to these environment variables